# ARK-Field v4.2 Cursor Guidelines

- Treat Git commit history as the primary structural source of truth.
- Route all event mutations through ingestion leader; do not bypass single-writer flow.
- Require Stability Kernel decision before executing network, automation, or publish actions.
- On any freeze/guard failure, switch to S2 baseline in one step.
- Keep event payloads canonical and deterministic (stable JSON field naming and hashing inputs).
- Prefer bounded execution (timeouts, burst caps, explicit retries).
- For NetWatch actions, disallow unbounded browser bursts and ungated external hooks.
- Keep modules orthogonal: adapters for IO, core logic in internal domain packages.
- Projection writes are append-only and replay-safe.
